    <detaileddescription>
<para>Tagged union implementation.</para>
<para>This Data union contains non trivial data types Map and Array, the default constructor and destructors are deleted by the compiler so we provided empty constructor and destructor just to pacify the compiler. The only job of this union to give a typed memory buffer to the <ref refid="structDali_1_1Property_1_1Value_1_1Impl" kindref="compound">Impl</ref> class which can construct the appropriate object using placement new. As <ref refid="structDali_1_1Property_1_1Value_1_1Impl" kindref="compound">Impl</ref> class explicitly construct the object and keeps track of the object it creates and then destroys them in the ~Impl() this will not leak any memory. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
